### ============================================
### DIJKSTRA TESTS - Shows profile differences
### ============================================

### 19a. REGULAR STUDENT: Entrance → Aula 103 (Dijkstra)
### Expected: Takes SHORTEST distance path
### Should avoid landmarks if they add distance
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/navigate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "startNodeId": 1,
  "endNodeId": 19,
  "userProfile": "Regular",
  "algorithm": "Dijkstra"
}

###

### 19b. NEW STUDENT: Entrance → Aula 103 (Dijkstra)
### Expected: Prefers path through LANDMARKS (Cafeteria★, Library★)
### May take longer route but passes through familiar reference points
### Landmark bonuses make landmark paths more attractive
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/navigate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "startNodeId": 1,
  "endNodeId": 19,
  "userProfile": "NewStudent",
  "algorithm": "Dijkstra"
}

###

### 20a. REGULAR: Parqueo → Aula 201 (Dijkstra)
### Expected: Direct shortest path
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/navigate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "startNodeId": 2,
  "endNodeId": 26,
  "userProfile": "Regular",
  "algorithm": "Dijkstra"
}

###

### 20b. NEW STUDENT: Parqueo → Aula 201 (Dijkstra)
### Expected: Route through landmarks (Entrance★, Cafeteria★, Library★)
### Will prefer passing through known reference points
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/navigate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "startNodeId": 2,
  "endNodeId": 26,
  "userProfile": "NewStudent",
  "algorithm": "Dijkstra"
}

###

### 21a. REGULAR: Junction → Admin Offices (Dijkstra)
### Shortest path only
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/navigate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "startNodeId": 3,
  "endNodeId": 10,
  "userProfile": "Regular",
  "algorithm": "Dijkstra"
}

###

### 21b. NEW STUDENT: Junction → Admin Offices (Dijkstra)
### May route through Cafeteria landmark first
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/navigate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "startNodeId": 3,
  "endNodeId": 10,
  "userProfile": "NewStudent",
  "algorithm": "Dijkstra"
}

###

### 22. WHEELCHAIR + DIJKSTRA: Multi-floor navigation
### Must avoid stairs, will use elevator/ramp
### Combines accessibility with optimal path finding
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/navigate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "startNodeId": 1,
  "endNodeId": 25,
  "userProfile": "Wheelchair",
  "algorithm": "Dijkstra"
}

